===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}

Composed of {{l|zh|田|t=cropland}} + {{l|zh|十|t=ten}} + {{l|zh|久|t=longlasting}}.

The {{l|zh|十}} + {{l|zh|久}} has been a shape change from earlier {{och-l|每}}. (Lin Yiguang)

===Etymology===
Possibly {{der|zh|sit}}. Compare {{cog|bo|རྨོ}}, {{m|bo|རྨོས||to plow}}, {{m|bo|རྨོད||t=plowing}}, {{m|bo|རྨོན་པ||plow-ox}}, {{cog|mjw|tr=-mò|t=classifier for strips of fields}} ({{zh-ref|Bodman, 1980}}; {{zh-ref|Baxter, 1992}}; {{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}). 

{{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}} also suggests a connection to an {{der|zh|aav}} root, probably with the semantics of “to enter; to insert”, whence {{cog|mkh-okm|cval||to enter; to penetrate; (of animals) to copulate}}, {{cog|kjg|tr=cmɔɔl|t=to plant (rice) with a digging stick}}, {{m|kjg|tr=crmɔɔl|t=digging stick}}. The semantic development would be “digging stick” > “plowing” > “acre”. He also connects this to {{och-l|牡|male animal}}; see there for more.

